    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - STANDARD SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>STANDARD SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the two (2) sets of tension springs and balls from housing bores and the anti-rotating
                pin have not been removed, place the shift bar housing on its side to remove them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301767">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301767" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301767" filename="../figg13/G1301767.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Standard Shifter Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay the assembly on a flat surface with the housing rear to the right (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301768">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301768" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301768" filename="../figg13/G1301768.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Remove Shift Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While removing the bottom yoke bar, remove the shift yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301768">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While removing the top yoke bar, remove the shift yoke assembly and block assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301769">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301769" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301769" filename="../figg13/G1301769.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Shift Yoke Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the interlock pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301770">Figure 70</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301770" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301770" filename="../figg13/G1301770.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Remove Interlock Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the middle yoke bar, remove the jam nut, plain nut, and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301770">Figure 70</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the range interlock bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301771">Figure 71</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301771" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301771" filename="../figg13/G1301771.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 71. Remove Range Interlock Bar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the select interlock bar from the middle yoke bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301772">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301772" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301772" filename="../figg13/G1301772.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Remove Shift Select Block</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the select tube to the left and remove the shift select block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301772">Figure 72</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the select tube with key to the left (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301773">Figure 73</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301773" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301773" filename="../figg13/G1301773.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Remove Select Tube</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, washer, spring and plunger from the 1st &#38; reverse shift yoke
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301774">Figure 74</hotlnk>). Remove the plug, spring, and plunger from the 3rd speed
                block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301775">Figure 75</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301774" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301774" filename="../figg13/G1301774.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Remove Snap Ring, Washer Spring &#38; Plunger</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1301775" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301775" filename="../figg13/G1301775.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 75. Remove Plug, Spring and Plunger</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the yoke and block parts; replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
